==English==

===Etymology===
French ''abatis'', ''abattis'', mass of things [[beaten]] or cut down, from ''abattre''. See [[Abate]]

===Spelling variants===
[[Abattis]]

===Noun===
'''abatis'''  (''plural:'' '''[[abatiss]]''')
#''(Fortifications):'' A means of defense formed by felled trees, the ends of whose branches are [[sharpened]] and directed outwards, or against the enemy.

